Hmm. It kinda depends on what they look like. I think when you say hybrid, a lot of people's mind goes straight to horrific mutant or something. Since we're obviously dealing with fantasy, I don't think that's really fair, but I do have some trouble trying to think of a hybrid that would look good. Like, if they're half-human, half-wolf, are they just, like... humans with wolf ears or tails? How much fur do they have? I'm not saying it couldn't look good, but I've never seen a good looking one.

I think a much cleaner system is the "Pokemon style" interspecies breeding, as it were. The offspring is always the species of the mother, but derives more mental stuff from the father. So, for example, if you had kids with a gray wolf lady with green eyes, while you yourself had brown hair and brown eyes, the kids would just be wolves with brown hair and brown eyes. And they would take more after your personality than her's, at least a little. That way, you still both see yourself in the children, and there's no risk of unsightly amalgams.
